CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 26, 1945, pg. 13 reads: "Tickets Are Out! - Dr. Lawrence Greenberger (far right), head of the Student Aid Committee of the Urban League, discusses the sale of tickets for the mammoth card party to be given June 14 at the YMHA [sic], Bellefield Avenue, with a member of the ticket committee, Mrs. Thomas Barton, while other workers look on. Left to right, seated: Mrs. Maurice Moss, Miss Eugenia Brunot and Mrs. aBrton [sic].  Standing: Herman McClane and Miss Evelyn Sherrer. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Mrs. Maurice Moss, Eugenia Brunot, and Mrs. Berton; standing: Herman McClane, Evelyn Sherrer, and Dr. Lawrence Greenberger, gathered around wooden bench in interior
